ub35.ezboard.com/ufaulk60.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faulk60</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 12:42:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> This is related to the earring quest (and probably other quests) so I'm putting it here.<br><br>I know there's four consilliums (four factions), but when you do quests there is never a &quot;shoulder of seru&quot; faction adjustment. Is the shoulder simply the one listed as &quot;seru&quot; or is that one for the Lord Seru himself?<br><br>I ask because I think it would be cool to drop down into the arx temple, not be KOS, and actually hail the Lord Seru, partly to investigate leads on the earring quest, but mostly to just hail him and see what's up with him <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Is this the &quot;seru&quot; faction? I've done many quests and gotten numerous +seru adjustments but am still scowling (did the grav flux thing and conned from the roof), so I'm wondering if anyone has gotten to dubious and how they did it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyalum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yalum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 3:48:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> [Thu Dec 13 19:35:41 2001] You say, 'who should'<br>[Thu Dec 13 19:35:41 2001] Brendar Mynden says 'The Shoulders of Seru are the workers and traders, bankers and merchants.  All of our industry is under the aegis of The Shoulders, and all of our trade as well.  They strive to make Sanctus Seru a prosperous enclave.  There is no shame in wealth, only in greed.<br><br>The Shoulders do have their own faction, they're just not closely allied with the Eye or the Hand, so doing quests for them don't always affect Shoulder faction.<br><br>Looking through my log, I've taken positive Shoulder hits for handing in zelniak meat, doing Examiner Maliken's quests all the way through, handing Centurion Jelin that note from brother, and by killing Recuso. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskecpataintedblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skecpa Taintedblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 7:18:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> Lord Inquisitor Seru has the same generic responses as the rest of Sanctus Seru, Including the generic response to 'Who is Seru' and 'Who is Katta' <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufaulk60.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faulk60</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 9:10:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> So Lord Seru isn't part of the 3rd earring quest? He just says &quot;greetings&quot; like everyone else? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umoosius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moosius</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 10:10:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> Faulk, i believe Seru is part of the Earring quest based on all the information given out by Talbik (sp) in Katta,  but probably not directly involved in the 3rd earring segment.  Pure speculation here... but i think that the 3rd earring is given out when you return the satchel with the 4 reports to Talbik at which time you get the 4th segment of the quest. I foresee a battle with Seru at the end of this quest.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufaulk60.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faulk60</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 10:23:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> And how exactly do you get the 4 reports? That's what everyone is trying to figure out, even if it means asking Lord Seru himself... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umoosius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moosius</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 12:20:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> That is the question eating away at us! Where to find the 4 reports....<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3538.topic">pub35.ezboard.com/fthesaf...3538.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucantatus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cantatus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/01 6:36:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Lord Inquisitor Seru has the same generic responses as the rest of Sanctus Seru, Including the generic response to 'Who is Seru' and 'Who is Katta'<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Everyone in the town seems to respond to 'Who is Seru/Katta?' the same, but certain people respond differently to '<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> What</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is Seru/Katta?'.  I'm specifically speaking about the Praeserti in Seru.  You can also ask the different Praeserti about each other which yields some humorous things. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskecpataintedblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skecpa Taintedblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/01 6:59:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> The Praesertum respond differently to &quot;Who is Seru&quot; and &quot;Who Seru&quot; differently. Without the Is they give generic response <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utyknee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyknee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/01 9:17:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru factions</span><hr size=1> I posted this in a back alley thread, but I wanted to repost it here.<br><br>I've found that the names of the mobs are VERY misleading as to what faction they are on, so do NOT trust the mob name. For example, the mobs in Marus Seru, named &quot;A Hand of Seru&quot; which con dubious to me, appear to be on Hand Legionaires faction (first hit on the list when killed). The mobs in Dawnshroud Peak, which I believed are named &quot;Legionaire XXX&quot; I'm going to assume are on the same faction (will kill one to verify). However the mobs inside Sanctus Seru, also named &quot;Legionaire XXX&quot; appear to be on Hand of Seru faction (again first hit when killed).<br><br>So, apply a little logic (which isn't 100% foolproof either), it would appear that the faction needed to clear the first set of guards is &quot;Hand of Seru&quot;. This faction can be raised by either killing Recursos in Marus Sactu (very green at 60, druid and paladin class mobs) or by killing Spire Sprites in Mons Letalis (a bit harder, some are light blue, Necros, and the zone is much more dangerous, however you get Citizen's faction with these and not with the recursos).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3543.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3559.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3597.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3597.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3597.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3597.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3597.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td 